No. 1.—Extract of a Letter from W. Warre, Esq, his Majesty's acting Consul at Porto, to Sir E. Nepean, dated 26th July, 1803,—I beg leave to mention that this coast is much annoyed by the enemy's small privateers; that they are fitted out from the neighbouring ports of Galicia;
